---
---
<section id="demos" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-20 fade-in">
      <div class="badge mb-5">See it in action</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary tracking-tight mb-5">
        Example conversations.<br/><span class="text-cal-gold">Representative tasks.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Flagship demo: Skill gap analysis — full width, with glow -->
    <div class="terminal mb-8 fade-in shadow-2xl shadow-black/30 ring-1 ring-white/[0.03] border-l-2 border-l-cal-gold">
      <div class="terminal-header">
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
        <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-secondary font-sans">openmind &mdash; skill gap analysis</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body space-y-4 text-[13px] md:text-sm">
        <div>
          <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
          <span class="text-text-primary"> What skills am I missing for AI PM roles?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Based on your resume and your goal of becoming an AI PM:
          <br/><br/>
          <span class="text-green-500">&check;</span> <span class="text-text-primary">Strong</span>: Python, ML fundamentals, NLP, data analysis<br/>
          <span class="text-green-500">&check;</span> <span class="text-text-primary">Strong</span>: Technical communication (from your BAIR research)
          <br/><br/>
          <span class="text-yellow-500">&triangle;</span> <span class="text-text-primary">Gap: Design/UX</span> &mdash; PMs need to evaluate UX and communicate with designers.<br/>
          <span class="text-text-muted">&ensp;&rarr; Take INFO 214 (User Experience Design) next semester</span>
          <br/><br/>
          <span class="text-yellow-500">&triangle;</span> <span class="text-text-primary">Gap: Business strategy</span> &mdash; no business courses on your resume.<br/>
          <span class="text-text-muted">&ensp;&rarr; Your Finance course helps. Focus on valuation frameworks.</span>
          <br/><br/>
          Your NLP + ML foundation is hella solid for AI PM roles. The gaps are fillable in 1&ndash;2 semesters. Fiat Lux! &#128161;
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Two side-by-side demos -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">

      <!-- Teach mode -->
      <div class="terminal fade-in fade-in-delay-1 shadow-lg shadow-black/20">
        <div class="terminal-header">
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-secondary font-sans">teach mode</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body space-y-3 text-[13px]">
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-text-primary"> Teach me about attention mechanisms</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            Think of reading a sentence. When you see &ldquo;it&rdquo; in &ldquo;The cat sat on the mat because it was tired&rdquo; &mdash; your brain looks back to figure out &ldquo;it&rdquo; = &ldquo;the cat.&rdquo; That's attention.
            <br/><br/>
            Quick check: if you have &ldquo;The bank was steep after the rain&rdquo; &mdash; which words would attention focus on to understand &ldquo;bank&rdquo;?
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-text-primary"> Steep and rain?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary">
            Exactly &#128293; That's how contextual embeddings resolve ambiguity.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Guided learning -->
      <div class="terminal fade-in fade-in-delay-2 shadow-lg shadow-black/20">
        <div class="terminal-header">
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-secondary font-sans">guided learning</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body space-y-3 text-[13px]">
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-text-primary"> /learn contextual integrity</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary">
            What do you already know about Nissenbaum's contextual integrity?
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-text-primary"> Something about privacy norms?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary">
            Good start! There are 3 independent parameters. If a doctor asks your age &mdash; that's fine. But if a stranger does? Same data, different <span class="text-text-primary">actors</span>. What's the second parameter?
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-text-muted">You &rarr;</span>
            <span class="text-text-primary"> The type of information?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary">
            Exactly &#128293; Medical data in a hospital = appropriate. Same data sold to advertisers = violation. That's <span class="text-text-primary">information type</span>. One more parameter &mdash; hint: think about <em>how</em> data flows.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
